The ChuoSeiki QT-series controllers use an RS232 interface. It does not require any special driver to run. However, if you connect the controller via a device such as a USB-RS232 converter, be sure to install its driver.

To download the QT-series controllers user manual, please follow this link, select the correct controller and download the manual under the Product information bar [http://www.chuo.co.jp/english/contents/hp0063/list.php?CNo=63]

'''Device Adapter initialization'''

When you select "ChuoSeiki XY Controller||XY stages", you will be asked to register the Serial port and Serial port setting.
When you select "ChuoSeiki Z Controller||Z stages", you will be asked to register the Serial port, Serial port setting, and Axis name.

The QT-series Serial port settings are as following:
